Program: Outlook
Title: 04/05/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00g9sv0
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 5 May 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, former islamic militant, Noman Benotman, reflects on his meetings with Osama Bin Laden and explains why he has now turned his back on militancy and tries to persuade others to do the same. We also hear from the Moroccan brothers who've won the world's toughest marathon no less than fourteen times. Show less